{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, this research aims to provide novice researchers with a clear understanding of the state-of-the-art results of CNNs in AHR, serving as a valuable resource for those entering the field.The main contributions of this work are:• Contextualizing CNNs in AHR Literature: While other reviews have explored DL techniques, none have exclusively focused on CNN-based methods in the context of AHR.",
    "We consolidate and analyze existing literature reviews on AHR, emphasizing the prominence of CNNs in recent studies.",
    "• Addressing Neglected Segmentation Phases: Previous reviews on Machine Learning (ML) or DL for AHR often neglected segmentation phases in AHR systems.",
    "In contrast, our review comprehensively covers both recognition and segmentation phases, providing a holistic view of the challenges and advancements in the field.",
    "• Coverage of Recognition Aspects: Our review spans the entire spectrum of recognition, encompassing digits, characters, and words."
  ]
}